# IGRP design system rules

This project uses `@igrp/igrp-framework-react-design-system`. All UI must follow the conventions documented in the canonical skill.

**Read `.agents/skills/igrp-design-system/SKILL.md` and follow its instructions** before writing any UI code. It documents:

- The three-layer picker: Horizon (`IGRP*`) → Custom → Primitives (escape hatch only)
- Hard rules: `'use client'`, `IGRPForm` + Zod for every form, semantic tokens only, `size-*` not `w-* h-*`, `flex gap-*` not `space-*`
- Common pitfalls (raw `<Input>` inside `IGRPForm`, raw palette colors, missing `'use client'`, etc.)

Deep references live alongside SKILL.md under `.agents/skills/igrp-design-system/references/` — load them on demand for the family you're working with:

- `forms.md` — `IGRPForm` + Zod + all `IGRPInput*` (load when any form is in scope)
- `data-table.md` — `IGRPDataTable`, `createIGRPColumnHelper`, the `actions` prop with typed row actions
- `charts.md` — `IGRPAreaChart` / `IGRPVerticalBarChart` / `IGRPLineChart` / … with `categoryKey` + `bars: IGRPBarConfig[]` + `valueFormatter: (n) => string`
- `horizon.md` — shared `IGRPInputProps`, naming conventions
- `primitives.md` — when to drop down, CVA variants
- `utilities.md` — `cn()`, `IGRPColors`, hooks
- `custom.md` — domain pieces

